langkawi-red-coral\/\" target=\"_blank\">\n                    <img class=\"lazypreload\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/23123138\/225437692-30x23.jpg\" alt=\"Red Coral Cottages\" height=\"300\" width=\"400\" data-src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/23123138\/225437692-450x338.jpg\">\n                    <div class=\"product__content\">\n                        <div class=\"product__content-subtitle\">Accommodation:<\/div>\n                        <div class=\"product__content-title\">Red Coral Cottages<\/div>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-arrow\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-arrow\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n                <\/a>\n            <\/div>\n        \n\n\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"besttime\">Best time to visit Langkawi<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Weather-wise, the best time to visit Langkawi is between January and March when it is the dry season. However, this will also be the peak tourist season.  <br>November to December and April to August can have a few drops of rain but there will be fewer tourists. <\/p>\n\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"Day 1 &#x2013; Langkawi from above &#x2018;Lang kawi&#x2019; means &#x2018;eagle red&#x2019;, as the island of Langkawi is famous for the many red-brown eagles living here. It&#x2019;s hard not to spot them during your time on the island. What better way to start your time on Langkawi, than by seeing it from a birds-eye view.&#xA0; 1. [&hellip;]","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":19481,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_relevanssi_hide_post":"","_relevanssi_pin_for_all":"","_relevanssi_pin_keywords":"","_relevanssi_unpin_keywords":"","_relevanssi_related_keywords":"","_relevanssi_related_include_ids":"","_relevanssi_related_exclude_ids":"","_relevanssi_r